The paper discusses the implementation of a reward-based synaptic sampling model on the SpiNNaker system, which is a neuromorphic computing platform designed for efficient execution of brain-inspired algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hardware accelerators and numerical optimizations, which could fall under the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The paper also mentions the potential applications of the SpiNNaker system in mobile and biomedical domains, which could fall under the sub-categories of Embedded Systems (cs.EM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
